[normal] Northern Ireland Screen is the lead agency in 
[normal]Northern Ireland
[normal] for the film, television and digital content industry.  It is supported by the Department of Culture, Arts &amp; Leisure and the Department of Enterprise, Trade and Investment in 
[normal]Northern Ireland
[normal] and manages Language funds on behalf of the Department of Cultu
[normal]re, Media &amp; Sport.  
[normal] Northern Ireland Screen is best known as the agency which attracted HBO’s Game of Thrones to be produced in 
[normal]Northern Ireland
[normal].
[normal] The BFI rated Northern Ireland Screen’s framework for screen education the best in Europe
[normal]